#DOC id=13--shorts-distribution source=/root/yvon/docs/briefs/lifeos-reference/13--shorts-distribution.md format=toon-doc compressed=2026-06-12T06:40:26.300Z

S|# 13 · Shorts (Distribution)|> Drop an edited short, and the copy + distribution gets prepared for every platform. A per-platform queue to push shorts everywhere.
S|Purpose|"Post & schedule your shorts — drop one clip, get a card for every platform, manage each queue." The owner drops an edited short; agents prepare the copy and distribution for all soc platforms; each platform has its own card/queue.
S|Page header|- Title: **Shorts**, breadcrumb `Vibe with AI / Shorts`. // - Sub-line: "Post & schedule your shorts — drop one clip, get a card for every platform, manage each queue."
S|Upload / drop zone|- A large **"Drop a short here"** dropzone with constraints noted (e.g. "MP4/MOV or WebM · up to 1080p · captures for YouTube, Instagram & TikTok generated"). // - **Choose file** button. // - A note that agents auto-gen platform captions from the dropped clip.
S|Per-platform queue|- **Platform filter chips**: **YouTube**, **LinkedIn**, **Instagram**, **TikTok** (with avatars and per-platform status). // - A row of **platform cards** — one card per platform for the current short, each with its own preview, generated copy, and **Status: Ready** (or pending) so each queue can be managed independently. // - A note like "make sure they're per-platform" / "drag a card from the Short pl" — i.e. cards arrive from the **Short pl** (`12`).
S|Workflow|Short pl prepares clip → drop into Shorts → per-platform captions/cards generated → rv/ready per platform → schedule (links into **Scheduler**, `15`) → distributed across YouTube/LinkedIn/Instagram/TikTok.